column1: #Text=( persian : استان تهران , transliteration : ostān-e Tehrān ) is a province in Central Iran .
#Text=It covers on area of 18,909 km ² and is located to the north of the central plateau of Iran .
#Text=This province has common borders with the Mazandaran province from north , Qom province from south , Semnan province from east and Qazvin province from west .
#Text=The province of Tehran has over 12 million inhabitants and is Iran 's most densely populated region .
#Text=Approximately 84.15 % reside in urban areas and 15.85 % in rural areas of the province .
#Text=The highest point of the province is Mount Damavand at an elevation of 5,678 m , and the lowest point of the province being the plains of Varamin , 790 m above sea level .
#Text=The largest Lakes of this province are Karaj River and Jajrud River .

#Text=Mountain ranges such as the Alborz span the north ; Savad Kooh and Firooz Kooh are located in the north east ; Lavasanat , Qarah Daq , Shemiranat , Hassan Abad and Namak Mountains are in the southern areas ; Bibi Shahr Banoo and Alqadr are situated in the south east and the heights of Qasr-e-Firoozeh being located to the east of the province .

#Text=Environmentally speaking , the climate of Tehran province in the southern areas is moderately warm , but in the mountain vicinity it is cold , and in the higher regions it is even colder with long winters and fairly large amounts of snow .
#Text=The hottest months of the year are from mid-July to mid-September when temperatures range from 28°C to 30°C , and the coldest months experience -10°C around December – January .
#Text=Tehran city has cold winters and hot summers .
#Text=Average annual rainfall is approximately 500 mm , the maximum being during the winter season .
#Text=- a small town outside of Tehran
#Text=- the oldest existing city in Tehran province
#Text=Palaces , museums , mosques , shrines , mausoleums and churches .
#Text=Golestan Palace , a UNESCO World Heritage site where the Peacock Throne of the Persian Shahs can be found .
#Text=The Tehran Museum of Contemporary Art features the works of great artists such as Van Gogh , Pablo Picasso and Andy Warhol .
#Text=Soltani Mosque , built by Fath Ali Shah
#Text=Mo'ezz o-dowleh mosque , built by Fath Ali Shah
#Text=Haj Seyd Azizollah mosque , built by Fath Ali Shah
#Text=Al-javad mosque , Iran 's first modernist design mosque .
#Text=The Old Sepahsalar mosque , another prominent Qajar-era mosque .
#Text=The new Sepahsalar mosque ( Madreseh e Motahari )
#Text=Javan-mard Qassab Mausoleum , a pre-Islamic semi-mythical hero
#Text=Dozens of Imam-zadeh shrines , hundreds of years old , including that of Imam Zadeh Saleh .
#Text=Ibn Babviyeh cemetery , where many Iranian giants such as Takhti and Ali Akbar Dehkhoda are buried .

#Text=Zahir o-dowleh cemetery , where many Iranian giants of art and culture such as Iraj Mirza , Mohammad Taghi Bahar , Forough Farrokhzad , Abolhasan Saba , Ruhollah Khaleghi , and Darvish-khan are buried .
#Text=The Polish cemetery north of Tehran , where World War II Allied soldiers are buried .
#Text=Parks and recreation are among the greatest things to do while you are in Tehran Province .
#Text=Here are things that might amuse you while you are in Tehran Province :
#Text=Tochal Skiing resort : is one of the best ski resorts around the world .
#Text=The French ( Poma ) built gondolas that carry tourists and skiers to Tochal mountain .
#Text=Within 10 minutes of driving distance from Tehran lies a ski resort .
#Text=Tochal is the world 's 4th highest ski resort at over 3,730 m ( 12,240 ft ) at its highest 7th station .
#Text=The resort was completed in 1976 shortly before the overthrow of the Shah .
#Text=Here , one must first ride the eight kilometres ( five mile ) long gondola lift which covers a huge vertical .
#Text=The resort 's longest slope is the south side U shaped slope which goes from the 7th station to 5th station .
#Text=The other two slopes are located on the north side of the 7th station .
#Text=Here , there are two parallel chair ski lifts that go up to 3,900 m ( 12,795 ft ) near Tochal 's peak ( at 4,000 m/13,125 ft ) , rising higher than the gondola 7th station .
#Text=This altitude is higher than any of the European resorts .
#Text=From the Tochal peak , one has a spectacular view of the Alborz range , including the 5,671-m ( 18,606 ft ) high Mt .
#Text=At the bottom of the lifts in a valley behind the Tochal peak is Tochal hotel , located at 3,500 m ( 11,483 ft ) altitude .
#Text=From there a T lift takes skiers up the 3,800 m ( 12,500 ft ) of Shahneshin peak , where the third slope of Tochal is .
#Text=Tochal 7th station has skiing eight months of the year .
#Text=But there are also some glaciers and year-round snow fields near Tehran where skiing began in 1938 , thanks to the efforts of two German railway engineers .
#Text=Today , 12 ski resorts operate in Iran , but the most famous are Tochal , Dizin , and Shemshak , all within one to three hours of Tehran .
#Text=Several caves , springs , and waterfalls outside Tehran .
#Text=Kebab shops are scattered all over the province .
#Text=If you are sick or not into kebab , there are lots of international restaurants in the city which range from Persian to Italian .
#Text=There are a lot of tea houses in the province , especially the capital .
#Text=Soft drinks such as cola , Fanta and Pepsi are also available .
#Text=The ZamZam Cola is the local Iranian cola .
#Text=Although alcohol is not allowed , it is drunk in some underground parties and weddings .
